{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1905e7c6-5e15-4ce2-956d-35d11b1770c0","content":"**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Here's what the test showed:\n\n```\nLength=3, Sum=6, sizeof(nint)=8\nnuint Length=2, Sum=141, sizeof(nuint)=8\n```\n\nThe only caveat: using `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context because `nint`/`nuint` don't have a **predefined** size (it's pointer-width — 8 bytes on this 64-bit machine). The `stackalloc` + `Span` part itself works fine without `unsafe`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c69ae24-b3b4-4c92-974e-4acf5e043f17","outputTokens":157},"id":"18f3925e-b915-4812-af84-f3e8246b9434","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:43:59.425Z","parentId":"6f0e92d2-2e9a-471a-9957-284d50b530ae"}
